            <h1>Michael's First Cheat Sheet</h1>
        </header>
        <article>
            <h2>Types of Elements to Match in CSS</h2>
            <table>
                <tr><th>Name</th><th>Definition</th></tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Type</td>
                    <td>A whole kind of element. (ex. p, h1, etc.)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Universal</td>
                    <td>Every element in the html</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Class</td>
                    <td>Can be added to an element. Makes it a little bit more specific and can be used for multiple elements.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ID</td>
                    <td>Very specific. An ID title should really only be used once.</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            <table>
                <h2>Calling back in CSS</h2>
                <tr><th>Name</th><th>Symbol</th></tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Type</td>
                    <td>No symbols. Just type the element type.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Universal</td>
                    <td>*</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Class</td>
                    <td>Prepend a "."</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ID</td>
                    <td>Prepend a "#"</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </article>
    </body>
</html>
